This was the worst experience we’ve had at a Morton’s and even a steakhouse in general. We sat at the bar to have dinner, expecting the typical great Morton experience. The drinks were made to order and our oysters were good, this is where things went downhill.  2 minutes after our oysters (order as an appetizer) arrived our dinner and 2 sides arrived, a total of  6 plates arrive all at once just for dinner. It was utter chaos. The baked potato we asked to split was not split, I had to separate the pieces onto different plates and then fillings were tossed on top carelessly (it literally made a mess), our steaks were half over done and half cooked to order, the scallops completely over done and we should have been told our dinner came with asparagus so we hadn’t ordered a side of asparagus. We were starving, literally the only meal of the day after working a conference, so we ate most of it out of pure hunger and knowing how much this all cost. When confronted about the very poor timing and food, the bartender (who served the food) didn’t care less. Poor fr, poor food, poor delivery. We will never visit another Morton’s no matter where it is.

This was a pretty bad experience. I ordered the lobster and I was very clear that I wanted it steamed.  I also specified that I did not want it broiled. Well it came broiled with the crispy top. The manager (Derek) was at the table when I asked the server why it was broiled? Once he saw that I wasn’t happy he left the table... this was very weird. I have never had a manager leave a server when they see an issue. My server Kale was very helpful she didn’t know or understand why it was broiled. She came back and told me the cook did steam my lobster then he broiled it for color. At this point the manager(Derek) still didn’t come back to the table to check on me. The server asked if she could have the cook make it again. I asked if he could just not put it in the broiler because I don’t like the tough top. She brought me a new lobster meal, it was cut up into four pieces. The manager(Derek) came by this time. I asked him why was the lobster cut into pieces. Derek told me that’s how I wanted it steamed, right? I said no. I wanted a nice lobster tail not tough lobster pieces. I pulled a piece out of the shell and asked him if he thought it was over cooked and he said he didn’t know how it was suppose to look. I still can’t get over the fact that Derek thought it was ok for the cook to cut up my lobster into four pieces!!! What kind of manager is this guy! Why is he at Morton’s? Derek was the worst manager ever. No restaurant should cut up your lobster into four pieces. I am disappointed and Morton should be ashamed. It was the worst meal and the service from Derek was even worst. Thank you Kale for trying to make our evening a good experience! Again, Derek was the worst and Morton’s should know that Derek is a bad representation of the restaurant.

The worse part is THEY WERENT EVEN PACKED!! This whole time while dining between us ladies having to borrow rolls of toilet tissue because after bringing up that it needs ATTENTION.. they just propped the roll instead of actually on dispenser. Keep in mind some stalls were disgusting so rolls were taken out of those and brought in others! Every time someone had use the facility u had check stalls track down those TWO ROLLS! Last time I just brought napkins I’d given up. Ofcourse management new, Ofcourse waiter knew and even though he knows he forgot us and our refills all night he was still tipped properly. As we are exiting the bottle of wine was not properly packaged and my husband took 3 steps with it and went thru bag shattering!!! Manager comes back again.. i calmly (almost tearing) informed him I HAVE NEVER EXPERIENCED nothing even close to this and I will NEVER VISIT THIS LOCATION. He gave me every excuse about public trash stalls and they were too busy, they had grave yard crew, excuse for EVERYTHING. I fired back if that was busy for them then they wouldn’t make it at other competitors near them!! I left their was 3 small tables!  3 hours in this restaurant. They should’ve declined my phone request for a reservation if they could not give the best possible experience. I feel like I paid for it!! I wrote a note also on my long receipt asking for another manager to call.. plus my email.. AND RADIO SILENCE. If they were the last upscale restaurant to go to.. I would consider BURGER KING!  Shame on Management for thinking it’s ok to service in that manner and expect us to pay too service price.

I felt quite important when asked if I would my bottle of water to be sparkling or "still. That is, until I saw that my still water was $6.50 for a bottle.  The general manager asked me how everything was, even though he saw that my food had just touched down on the table, and that I didn't even have my napkin in place, and so I could not have even taken one single bite of anything. But he was very friendly, engaging, and attentive, the rest of the night. So although I did take notice of all of that, I did let that one pass.  The two women at the front were absolutely engaging, friendly, respectful, and efficient. One took my reservation, the other seated me, and joked back with me, when I engaged her.  Both those women, and the bussers that were clearing the table had courtesy that could teach the wait staff a thing or two. Ordered a “medium” bone-less rib-eye, got a steak that was so well done it could of only come from a straight A cow!  While waiting on my meal, my entertainment for the evening was watching the cook play on his phone the entire time I was there.  One can only assume he was attempting the latest high score or keeping his many Facebook followers up to date on his latest culinary disaster.  The waiter was attentive at first, but after the main course was served he was harder to locate than Waldo!  Someone, I can only assume was the manager because they never introduced themselves, asked how the meal was.  My coworker was able to answer but I mid bite, and raised with good manners, was unable to respond.  The ability of staff to vanish at this restaurant is astounding as the manager vanished just as quickly as the waiter.  If you care about good steaks cooked right, and staff that do their jobs you are better off finding another steakhouse.  Morton’s at 6:30pm is not busy there was no reason any of this should of happened other than staff that simply don’t care.  If they don’t than you really should take your business to better steakhouses in New Orleans.
